SET UP DJANGO


1.) make sure python is installed

2.) pip install virtualenv

3.) mkdir Django_Venv, cd Django_Venv

4.) virtualenv .

5.)cd scripts

6.) type activate


7.) type pip install django and then cd to github repo folder

8.) cd webapp\src


9.) python manage.py runserver


10.) on browser goto 127.0.0.1:8000




SETUP IPFS + TESTRPC

1.) open new cmd console

2.) testrpc -u 0


3.) open new cmd console

4.) run ipfs init (if not already)

5.) new console (again)

6.) ipfs config --json API.HTTPHeaders.Access-Control-Allow-Origin "[\"*\"]"

7.) ipfs config --json Gateway.HTTPHeaders.Access-Control-Allow-Origin "[\"*\"]"

8.) keep the testrpc,ipfs and webserver terminals open.

9.) goto 12.0.0.1:8000


enjoy



congrats!